<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: Going out on a limb on looting</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Craig">Craig</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:55 p.m. 15/6/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: Going out on a limb on looting<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2144" TARGET=_self>Going out on a limb on looting</A> (Ice)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I think the should do the inventory loot thing as you say.

<P>But FIRST....
<BR>They should run the following poll:
<P>Which method of loot do you favor:
<BR>1. Any one non-equipped item (may be from containers)
<BR>2. Looters choice of either
<P>* Any one item (not a container)
<P>* Rip a spell (page) from the victim's spell book to make the spell scroll. (Which may be scribed or sold as if it were the original scroll)
<P>If the looter chooses option 2, then the spell caster looses the spell.
<P>I don't see #2 winning, but it would at least make the spell casters think thank God when they choose to change the looting method to #1 :)
<P>Craig
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
